LOWER INVENTORY GENERATED $116 MILLION OF CASH MAINLY DUE TO SUPPLY CHAIN OPTIMIZATIONS AND LOWER COMMODITY COSTS. INVENTORY DAYS ON HAND INCREASED 4 DAYS PRIMARILY DUE TO FOREIGN EXCHANGE IMPACTS.

